## 1. Overview

This document defines every file, folder, content specification, and behavioral requirement for the `copilot-data-analysis-lab` GitHub repository. It is the single source of truth for building this lab. Nothing should be invented or improvised; if it is not specified here, it should not be built.

This lab follows the same structural DNA as:
- `copilot-analyst-lab` (Lab 1) — RIFCC prompting + artifact-driven stages
- `copilot-analyst-documentation-lab` (Lab 2) — custom agents + LAB_ACTION_GUIDE runbook style

This lab extends that DNA by introducing:
- RIFCC-DA (Data Analysis variant of RIFCC)
- Agent Modes (mindset-switching, not necessarily technical agents on day one)
- A real synthetic dataset with intentional imperfections
- Jupyter notebook artifact output
- Responsible-use embedded at start AND end (not just a checkbox)

