#### Stage-Specific Review Criteria

**Stage 0 (Risk Review):**
- [ ] All columns assessed for sensitivity level
- [ ] email_masked flagged as requiring caution
- [ ] At least 3 handling recommendations documented
- [ ] Stated what data must NOT appear in outputs

**Stage 1 (Profiling):**
- [ ] Row count documented
- [ ] Null counts per column documented
- [ ] At least 8 data quality issues identified
- [ ] Copilot assumptions documented separately from verified facts
- [ ] Code reviewed before execution

**Stage 2 (Cleaning):**
- [ ] Justification written for every row drop or imputation
- [ ] Row count before AND after cleaning documented
- [ ] No irreversible operations without a backup copy
- [ ] Cleaning script commented line-by-line
- [ ] Edge cases addressed (negative values, nulls, format inconsistencies)

**Stage 3 (EDA):**
- [ ] Business question answered in plain English
- [ ] All percentages cross-checked
- [ ] No causal claims without evidence
- [ ] Assumptions explicitly listed
- [ ] Limitations explicitly listed

**Stage 4 (Visualization):**
- [ ] All chart axes labeled with units
- [ ] No distorted or truncated Y-axis
- [ ] No 3D charts
- [ ] email_masked column not visible in any chart
- [ ] Charts have titles
- [ ] Legend matches data

**Stage 5 (Audit):**
- [ ] All scripts reviewed for external calls
- [ ] No hardcoded sensitive values
- [ ] Transformations are justified and reversible
- [ ] Output would pass an internal code review
- [ ] Risk findings documented

**Stage 6 (Executive Summary):**
- [ ] Exactly 3 key insights (no more, no less)
- [ ] Exactly 2 actionable recommendations
- [ ] At least 1 explicit risk note
- [ ] At least 1 data limitation disclaimer
- [ ] Written for a non-technical executive audience

