## 6. Behavioral and Design Constraints

### Consistency with existing labs
- LAB_ACTION_GUIDE.md must use the same section formatting and tone as Lab 2
- RIFCC-DA must be a natural extension of RIFCC from Lab 1 — same acronym, same 5 fields
- Success criteria checklist must mirror Lab 1's end-state checklist format

### No shortcuts
- Every stage must have a review checklist
- Every stage must have a hand-off checkpoint
- Every artifact must have a corresponding template
- The prompt pattern must appear in EVERY agent mode file

### Data handling principles
- The CSV must never contain real data
- The `email_masked` column intentionally tests whether participants treat it as sensitive — it should look realistic but be fully synthetic (e.g., `j***@g***.com`)
- No column should be named "password", "ssn", or "credit_card" — the sensitivity test must come from realistic ambiguity, not obvious red flags

### Technical constraints
- All Python code must use only: pandas, matplotlib, seaborn, numpy
- No external library installs required at runtime
- Notebooks must use relative paths (`../data/`) not absolute paths
- All markdown must be valid GFM (GitHub Flavored Markdown)

